text: Magnus Landin Jacobsen (born 20 August 1995) is a Danish handballer for THW Kiel and the Danish national team.EHF profile He is the younger brother of Niklas Landin Jacobsen. ==Playing career== Landin won the 2013 Men's Youth World Handball Championship along the Danish youth national team, defeating Croatia 32–26 in OT. In 2013 Jacobsen signed with Nordsjælland Håndbold transferring from HIK. In 2014 it was announced that the talented left wing had signed a two-year contract with KIF Kolding København starting at the begin of the 2014/2015 season. He won his first Danish championship the first year at KIF Kolding Copenhagen. On 17 November 2017, KIF Kolding København announced that Magnus would leave the club at the end of the 2017/2018 season. Later same day, it was announced that he would join THW Kiel on a two-year contract starting at the begin of the 2018/2019 season. Landin made debut for the Danish national team on 10 June 2015 in a match against Lithuania. ==Honours== *Danish Championship: **: 2015 ==References== ==External links== * Category:1995 births Category:People from Gladsaxe Municipality Category:Living people Category:Danish male handball players Category:KIF Kolding players Category:THW Kiel players Category:Expatriate handball players Category:Danish expatriate sportspeople in Germany Category:Handball- Bundesliga players
